Pruning in Unigram (SentencePiece) and rare token handlingYes, pruning could risk losing rare but relevant tokens, but the algorithm is designed to minimize this. Unigram starts with a large seed vocabulary (common substrings or oversized BPE) and uses an Expectation-Maximization (EM) process on a unigram language model. It iteratively removes tokens whose removal increases the overall corpus log-likelihood the least (i.e., least useful for explaining the data).

